place_description: Quaint cafe/bar in the McGill Rose Garden with hot drinks, craft beer & wines, plus photo sessions.

reviews_data.review_text: Although the food is a food truck outside, the drinks are very good and the bartenders are very sweet. For me the highlight was pure awe as I walked out the gallery door finding a complete world of beauty and nature outside. Small private nooks within a vast overgrown secret garden with the echoes of soft music from a great musician who truly created a magical atmosphere. We will definitely be back, I will definitely be back!
A beautiful venue! So many spots to sit and have a drink and great food truck options! A must visit in Charlotte! Parking can be limited.

What a great spot ! Met friends for drinks before going to dinner . Outside seating is very organic with lots of greenery and flowers .  There is a small amount of seating inside . Wine selection is interesting and all that we tried was really good .  Would definitely recommend !

I love Rosie's but wow, this is my first time coming back in a few months and this new employee definitely knows how to talk. Her personal conversations bellow throughout the small space making it impossible to focus on any work or even relaxation for that matter. I tried to put in headphones and still could hear her through them. While I know she isn't intentionally doing so, I find that she is completely unaware of her surroundings and lacks respect for the customers. At one point I was here 7 days a week almost and this has certainly effected my want to come back. I could tell you every conversation she had... from her L'occitane body wash to her annoyances at the DMV and passport arrival times, I could write an entire essay on every conversation she had. I understand being quite at work may not be the most "fun" but when a great deal of people are working on things here, her lack of consideration for this is upsetting. I have left a 5 star review as I don't want this to affect the companies ratings, rather just a note for improvement.
Tea, coffee, wine, and beer options with an adorable atmosphere!! What's not to love?! Great spot for a picnic- BYO food!!

Such a great date spot or girls night spot! Atmosphere is so cute inside and out! Wilder was so knowledgable on wine and helps us pick out the best one for our palates. 100% recommend if you love wine and great service! (Note they also have beer and seltzer too if wine is not your cup of tea).
The best place for outdoors nature wine chips and games
Wine was ok, beautiful place.. def plan to come back with friends
Gorgeous secret garden! Great coffee and wine spot!
That was to bad .
Great place for a relaxed drink.

Cannot say enough good things about this place. Such a warm, welcoming, and cute atmosphere. All of the staff is very kind and helpful- not to mention they make delicious (and affordable) coffee. Pastries are good when they're available. Garden is also soo pretty, just another bonus of coming here.

My favorite: Rosie's partners with an organization called UMAR that works with individuals with developmental disabilities, who come to the garden to paint and learn how to garden. Their artwork and the herbs they plant can be purchased- all proceeds go to the organization that supports these individuals.

All around amazing place with amazing people- best coffee shop I've ever been to!
This is a unique gem they do not have food but they do entertain food trucks . You actually get to sip on coffee or wine while hanging out in a garden they also have trivia ! This is a must visit
Best spot in clt for coffee or wine!
Rosies used to be a great way to spend a beautiful afternoon surrounded by amazing plants, that is no longer the case
Great food, great service and environment but you have to wait more than 40 mnt to get your food
It looks like most of the roses have been picked by greedy patrons sipping wine.
Such a cute place to hang out! The garden is beautiful and they have a decent wine selection

Rosie's is an amazing hidden gem in Charlotte. It is beautiful in the afternoon and magical at night with all the twinkle lights. A perfect date spot with stellar staff. They also do live music, trivia, and some other events here as well!
Amazing atmosphere and service. I absolutely love it here, must see in Charlotte!

What a great concept! Coffee, wine, beer, dog friendly all amidst a beautiful garden of plants, some of which are for sale. Charlotte doesn't have too many unique options but this one definitely stands out. Love it.
I love the out door garden
We were first timers and had general questions, the staff seemed a lil annoyed and rude. Besides that I think the outside garden area is very beautiful.
Thanks s was my first visit to Rosie's. A great place to enjoy a glass of wine or a beer on a Sunday afternoon.

LOVE Rosie's!!! I rarely ever drink coffee but always love coming here and getting a matcha - they have both sweetened or unsweetened which is a huge plus! The staff are always so friendly and helpful. Not to mention the garden is absolutely beautiful and the perfect place to sit outside and get work done or study!
I loved it there, it was amazing night I had latte and my sister had beer. They have wifi access. Love the garden. Fresh air with beautiful flowers.
I had wine and it was of good quality  just could have been more in the glass
Love coming here with friends!
Such a beautiful atmosphere here, especially during the holidays.

Such a cute little place! The garden was so amazing, lush, and inviting. The drinks and pastries were yummy. Service was great, everyone was very kind and welcoming. Had such a delightful time. Definitely has to be a regular place for me
Rosie's is the perfect spot to just chill and hang out with friends. Their garden is so cute and cozy
Verdant peaceful oasis near the heart of the city - great staff serving coffee or wine or other drinks / five stars!
Great space well kept patio with plenty of seating and the sparkly selection was delicious
Great service
We went here on Wednesday night and it was wonderful! The garden is so gorgeous and spacious, it's the perfect location for a friend gathering or date. Would highly recommend!
Why the recent price increases?
Cute place.  Didn't eat anything, but was there taking pictures for my daughter's wedding.

A real hidden gem in downtown Charlotte.

Both a coffee bar and wine bar located on over 2 acres of urban garden.

As you enter,you have no idea what is in the back. You order your coffee or wine ( We had beer..lol) and then you can stroll thru the gardens or just sit on one of the many sitting areas thru our the gardens.

We went on a Sunday afternoon and waited about 15 minutes to order our drinks. There are no food options other than a few bags of snacks they sell along with bottles of wine.

A real quant cafe/bar in Charlotte that is worth a visit.

This is definitely a hidden gem in the Charlotte area as it's ideal for families, private events, or remote work sessions. Its tranquil setting offers a refreshing escape from city life, creating a pleasant and relaxed atmosphere. It's perfect during summer and fall and to watch sunsets.
There was a taco truck outside, delicious .The Atmosphere was a whole vibe, wine was great, people were friendly. Good time
This is an absolute gem! Great wine & beer selection with an atmosphere second to none.
I spent a good time wandering the adjacent historic gardens. So beautiful

Such a cute spot in Charlotte! The coffee they serve is delicious and you can't go wrong with any of their wine selections. Great place for a quick work meeting or taking a lil mental break and read a book outside in their beautiful garden. I'd give 10 stars if I could!!

No words really. The staff is beyond loving, warm, professional. This is my safe space. This is a fantastic place to bring clients as a broker. It is beautiful for a date. To sit and have coffee with a friend. This place makes every day special. I am not kidding. Rosies is magic. Oh, & I didn't know, but overflow parking is in the apartments in the back!

I attended the gallery in the garden event at Rosie's it's such an amazing gem in Charlotte. I got a chance to speak with the owner (husband) he was very knowledgeable and helpful with explaining everything. I'll definitely be back. The garden is beautiful.

I went here twice when visiting Charlotte and had a great experience both times! The coffee is great and I loved being able to work from the space comfortably. I didn't eat anything, so I can't rate the food, but would definitely go back in the future.

Sure cute! Sat outside in their natural gardens. Cozy place with nice ambiance. The patio has heat lamps, lots of places to sit (patio and picnic tables) all scattered about. Ordered a tea and just journaled outside.
Amazing atmosphere. Noele and Ms. Koko gave excellent wine recommendations my party and I enjoyed! And even helped us with serving recommendations for our group. I will be returning.
This place has non-stop traffic which is great and lots of places to sit outside. Good coffee and great service.

Wonderful garden escape on the edge of Uptown with an excellent selection of wine and service was so friendly. Bring your own picnic or favorite tapas and enjoy the gardens by day and the lights by night. My Mom was visiting and loved it!
Beautiful place and great coffee and drinks.
Great place especially in the spring.
The garden is adorable. This place is a gem
I didn't like this place when I went. The server "Koko" was rude. Wouldn't recommend ever.
Amazing atmosphere for our wedding! The gardens are beautiful and wonderful drink options!

Awesome atmosphere and polite service. For the large garden in the back with outdoor seating, and free parking, I would enjoy coming back here on a regular basis if I could. The white chocolate raspberry latte I had was very good, as were our lavender scones. Highly recommended!

Awesome atmosphere and great customer service. Upon the barista's recommendation I got the almond milk honey latte with half honey.
She knew what I wanted more than I did!!
Super delicious. The outside was just as lovely as the inside.
Will come back!
Love love love the garden!! Especially in the summer. And in the winter they have heaters and fire pits
Favorite cafe in Charlotte

I make sure to stop by Rosie's every time I am visiting in Charlotte. I love the atmosphere they've created, it feels cozy, creative/artsy, chill and the garden tops it. I wish more places followed this concept. The oatmilk latte was super tasty!

Stopped by while visiting Charlotte for the weekend. Had an amazing salted honey latte that was very delicious. They have a garden sitting area in the back that provides a great atmosphere for enjoying a coffee or glass of wine. I would definitely come back next time I'm in the area.
Special place
Nice staff and cozy atmosphere. Will visit again.

Beautiful spot to relax and enjoy the outdoors -- even in the winter.

Plant based milk alternatives for coffees.
Great selection of drinks: both alcoholic and non alcoholic.

Parking is limited.
We did Tuesday night trivia. It was fun. They had us outdoors with heaters on.
I loved the warm vibes I felt like I was in a garden lol and the employees had smiles the whole time I only went for water and to see inside I'll be back

Stopped by to check out Hot boys chicken food truck, so glad we did! The food was sooo delicious & cooked perfectly. We loved how you could pick up your order & enjoy it around all the holiday lights! This place is such an adorable hidden gem, will be returning soon!
Great spot, whether a date or large groups. Fantastic environment. Outside of parking, it's a breeze.

I visited Rosie's with a few girlfriends to grab a glass of wine.The atmosphere is so dreamy and romantic, and the wine was delish!

We unfortunately misplaced a set of car keys before the night was over, and Wilder (a team member of Rosie's) went above and beyond to help us look for them. She was so patient and caring. Service like her's is another reason to visit this beautiful place.
Beautiful atmosphere and knowledgeable staff.
Amazing atmosphere I love this place so much!
Great atmosphere! Great wine !
A hidden gem in Noda. I did not expect the garden to be as big as it is. Lots of seating areas, lighting at night is nicely done. Apart from the wines and beers, they serve coffee till late night.
We were given a gift of wine tastings class. What a wonderful experience and enjoyed the evening. Cannot wait to schedule our next class!

It's prettier in photos. But it is nice, very good atmosphere, quiet and comforting place. The people who work there are very helpful and nice. They have an art gallery with a very beautiful work of charity and humanity.
unreal coffee and the best setting in CLT hands down
Truly a hidden gem in Charlotte! I liked hanging out at Rosie's so much I became a barista here!
Best Barista in town!  Amazing coffee. Emma's smile always brightens our mornings!
My absolute favorite spot in Charlotte. A hidden gem in the middle of the city. Great coffee and even better atmosphere!

Rosie's is such a cute and lovely place. It's adorably decorated, coffees are delicious, and the wine selection is fabulous. I love the art inside the shop. How much better can the outside be with it being the McGill's Rose Garden? It's just a perfect setting with the flowers and garden art. There is plenty of seating in the garden, including tables with benches as well as other seating scattered throughout. I was lucky enough to host friends and family at Rosie's to celebrate my daughter's high school graduation earlier this summer. The staff is amazing and accommodating. Everyone raved about what a great place it is. It's a little hidden gem right off Uptown and 277 and is well worth a visit. Parking is limited on-site but there's plenty just around the corner and within a quick walk. They also have cute cat swag. Just the best place to relax with a glass of wine or a cup of coffee.

So this place is super cute. I used to live in Austin and this place reminds me of a tucked away spot on South Congress or the Hill Country. I like the small intimate bar area. I enjoyed the garden and it's serenity. The staff are great, the coffee was good, and the wine selection was interesting. Honestly, I'd go back for the coffee, not the wine. The atmosphere and ambiance made the wine bearable. I think anyone looking for a quiet spot to relax in the afternoon will find this place fits the bill. If you're looking for a place to hang with friends and take unique photos, you've got the right spot. They offer photography passes which I find to be a very unique way to finance the upkeep of the grounds (Fully support it). I'll definitely go back because I'm a garden lover.
This place is a hidden gem...i found inspiration for my backyard  in the garden. The service was excellent too!
The most amazing place to share a conversation while sipping on wine or coffee.  A beautiful garden in Charlotte.  The staff was completely in touch with their guests.  I loved my Rocket Fuel!!!!
Super fun and unique spot!

Visited for the first time during the art gallery Rosie's was hosting--  I loved the outdoor garden (though interior design was wonderful) , had a great wine selection, awesome drinks. Our barista Coco(?I believe that was her name, she was tall) was super-friendly, quick, and extra helpful. Naturally, the event had the staff busy, but the line was extra quick, even with the patrons lining up outside.

As a coffee fanatic, I definitely recommend the Berries & Creme they have as a special-- nice balance of sweetness and coffee.  My only "complaint", if you could call it that, was the baked goods selection was a little limited by the time we arrived, but with the amount of people they were accommodating, that's hardly their fault.

TLDR; Definitely will be returning soon. Great coffee & alcohol worth more than they charge, and the entire garden is a vibe. Shout out to Coco, she's a rockstar. Try the Berries & Creme!
What a secret gem. The garden was gorgeous! I absolutely loved it and want to go back soon!

I'm so sad it took me so long to get to Rosie's Coffee and Wine Garden in Charlotte NC! Such an amazing space!! We ended up going in the afternoon for coffee! They had so many different options for coffee- lattes, iced, espresso plus many milk and syrup options! DEFINITELY try the rosemary! They have indoor and outdoor seating! They also have wine by the glass and bottle and a selection of beers and other beverages. I'm def going back for $5 wine night on Tuesdays!! I'm going back again regardless! The outdoor space was expansive! Lots of shade and seating and there is a herb garden! Did I mention they are dog friendly inside and out? Can't wait to go back for another fantastic experience!!!
One of the best wine bars in Charlotte.
A sactuary hidden within the busy concrete jungle life of Charlotte.

Such a beautiful great place, the garden is spectacular and it is an ideal place to be and enjoy nature around, I don't drink but there are several options of drinks, I had an ice matcha latte with rosemary syrup that I prepared a very nice barista and it was delicious, I was with a friend talking but I can definitely go back on my own to read or color, try the food or get another tea and wrap myself in such beautiful environment
Came for a trip to ATL. Deja was our server who had Amazing customer service!  Food was fresh and fast.
Beautiful coffee shop and garden! Lovely to peruse the grounds and get lost in the blooms and greenery! Grab a coffee or tea, sit in the backyard garden!
5 stars all the way.

This place is a hidden gem! Highly recommend! And you can order food to be delivered from optimist hall to the wine garden. Staff is amazing and the vibes are great! Half off bottles of wine on Wednesday!
Hippest place in Charlotte. Sweet scene with sweet people.
A tranquil respite from the busy city. Gorgeous gardens, tasty coffees, and I'm sure the wine is divine (though I've yet to try it).

4 stars for food as most of the times they are out of baked goods.

Overall amazing atmosphere and you can find a lot of semiprivate spots in the garden. Coffee is good and a great selection of wine.

Make sure you check the special event schedule,  because sometimes they are closed for special events.
Love coming here with friends to grab a glass or bottle of wine! You can bring your dog and outside food in! Pack a picnic and stay for a while. They also have fun games inside.
Lovely place, impressive selection.  What a joy to finally attend.

SO CUTE! My friends and I came here for the first time to celebrate a birthday and we were immediately welcomed by the sweetest woman who helped us in choosing a wine for the night.

The staff had a lot of knowledge and understanding of the tastes and pairings for the wines they offered. The atmosphere was DARLING. We went on a week night and it there was plenty of seating and private, quiet  spots. A lot of people studying or working and some chatting.

As we were leaving, we were told they sometimes have events and vendor markets in the center garden.

We will definitely be returning!
Wonderful atmosphere!

I am a professional wedding photographer that has done multiple shoots here and it never disappoints!  The folks that work here are amazing and are 2nd to none when it comes to service and kindness.  They always treat my team and I like we're part of the family.  The venue itself is so beautiful and is the perfect background for your wedding day, or any kind of shoot you want to have there.  I've added some photos from some of my shoots, enjoy!
Parking lot is not greatest! But this venue was amazing
Beautiful place inside and out. It's an oasis in the middle of Charlotte.
What a delightful venue!  Had a fantastic time! So many beautiful places to sit and enjoy.
We stopped by for a wonderful coffee and enjoyed the lovely gardens in back.
I love Rosie's! Friendly staff and beautiful space.
Awesome bar, bring your own food. Totally different vibe at night!
Great place to explore.  The garden out back is huge.  The wine is slightly over-priced when compared to other nearby beer and wine stores, but the entire garden experience makes up for the price.

Simply beautiful!
Hidden gem in the city,
Coffee and wine walks.
Love this coffee and wine bar in a beautiful historic garden!
Just the best place on earth. Coco was amazing! She took great care of us!!!
Super cute! Very family friendly.

I LOVED it here. Employees were so kind and attentive. Helped me figure out where I could sit in the shade since I'm a redhead. The wine and scone were delicious. And such a peaceful place to study for the afternoon. Will definitely be returning

This place was a very very pleasant surprise. From the street I expected a cozy little wine and tea house in a historic building. And yes, it's exactly that. BUT ALSO the back garden is expansive, well-cultivated, beautifully lit, and hosts a plethora of events. It was a wonderful place for a rendezvous, but it would be just as pleasant for a quiet cup of tea and a book. It's got all the warm, pleasant, inclusive ambience I could have asked for. Also, the staff are very lovely, friendly, authentic human beings. Thanks all, for a lovely evening!

One of the top hidden gems in Charlotte. Great staff with an even better drinks menu. But obviously the grounds steal the show. A beautiful, quiet space with a variety of areas to find a place to sit and relax.
Great wine selection, beautiful urban garden to relax in. Live music, art.
Incredible ambiance!
Staff is very friendly! The garden is peaceful and lovely.

Rosie's is a fantastic spot tucked away in plain sight. It's in the heart of NoDa and has a HUGE outdoor seating and garden area.

They have a great list of craft beer, wine, and a reasonable selection of coffee drinks. Not much in the way of food/snacks.

Great place to meet on a beautiful day for work, meetings or social engagements of any type.
Very nice place to go and relax
Went there for trivia on a Tuesday. Decent selection of wine. I didn't try the coffee. Their outdoor area is essentially a garden with quite a bit of seating.
Pricey but very nice

It's a beautiful area to sit outdoors and enjoy nature and sit with friends, grab a coffee or wine. It's ok for taking photos also but at the right time. Spring and summer the flowers bloom so I'd be weary of the massive amount of bees that are there doing their job with the flowers. Other than that it's a cute little hide away to try out if you need a good spot to get away and breathe the outdoor air and be calm.
Soooo cute. Very quiet and peaceful during the day
I love this place

I've been to this place so many times and it's always amazing. The staff is super helpful in picking out wine and they always have great selections. Ambiance outside is incredible and they have great musical talent come. Limited indoor seating but dog friendly in and outside.
Beautiful secret gem, wine, coffee and friendly service. Instagram worthy for sure!
beautiful place!!! great coffee & drinks. you can host special events here as well
Super cozy wine bar with great coffee too! Trivia on certain nights too!
Convenient
A wonderland, truly!

The gardens themselves are beautiful! Atmosphere is is lovely.

However, having an event here is not the easiest. I was not the one who was hosting, but my friend was. I helped her set everything up & brought everything in prior to guests arriving. When we got there the seats were dirty, they looked like they had mildew all over them. I asked if they could be wiped down and the manager Jason (I think) yelled to someone on staff "Hey! Can you wipe the seats down again, apparently they're still dirty even though we already wiped them down" I defended my ask by saying they looked like they were outside when it rained & I was able to flick dried whatever it was off of the chairs. I was also told they were stored inside- wrongo- they are stored in their outside storage pod- so yes, outside so they were mildewy.

Jason proceeded to tell me that they had them professionally assessed & they can't be cleaned anymore they are permanently  like that. Which tells me, they are permanently dirty.

Then the catering arrived- which was some Publix deli looking sandwiches with no name cards so everyone had to guess what was in each sandwich. There was no cutlery, regular sized plates or the basic condiments that go with sandwiches. Then the wine that was previously selected for the menu was changed but no one informed the host. She found out by going to the bar to order wine & realized what she selected with the venue was not available so the event manager changed it to a wine that the host specifically asked to NOT have out.

The venue did not provide heating lamps, without a cost, although is a venue that is mostly outside. There was little to no light in the actual event space, the string lights & t-light candles can only do so much. The trash cans were full of trash from the last event, so we had to ask for them to be cleaned out.

As someone who works in the event & hospitality industry professionally, I might be a little picky. But my friend spent $750 + the required F&B min (which was over $1,000) on an experience that was not worth more than $500.

Was honestly disappointed on how a venue that hosts small scaled events regularly presented themselves so rudely & obviously disorganized. Which is a shame because the venue space is lovely- its everything else surrounding that made the experience not pleasant.
Love everything about this place and it's completely free!!!
Love the little wine shop they have, all while being able to enjoy their garden to hangout!
Was here for a wedding great venue and environment, smallish parking area but it's near uptown so to be expected

Rosie's Wine Garden is one the best spots in Charlotte. Beautiful gardens that are more expansive than you would expect, it's nice to wander and discover new little pockets to sit. They have a good selection of wine and their service is always quick. We take everyone who visits us in Charlotte here as it truly is a gem.
Beautiful garden with wine. Bring in your own food and enjoy!

This place is everything. The ladies behind the bar are super friendly and helpful, there is a wide variety of drinks for ALL of your friends I had a strawberry rhubarb sour that was amazing and as I left I grabbed the seasonal Chai and apple cider blend that was absolutely top notch. On top of all of that the gardens are absolutely gorgeous. We got lucky and it was rainy today so it was almost completely empty and it was magical. I can't wait to go back!
Great spot for a date, girls night, or just chilling. Fire pits are super nice now that it's getting chillier. Half-priced bottled on Wednesday are excellent.
Loved it

Carol, the associate who assisted us, did a FANTASTIC job!!  She brought out 2 wines that matched my requested style AND a 3rd bonus suggestion that was very, very good!! We were able to sample all 3 wines before deciding..  They also had vegan brownies and cookies!

The prices were quite reasonable too.
Beautiful setting! You should come by for a sit
Really nice and very unique place! We will be back, though we liv e 40 miles away!

Absolutely beautiful at night, especially during spring or fall! Great place to go for a really cute date or just a good time together. Plenty of seating in brightly lit areas, as well as cozy romantic corners as well. If you're going on the weekend, I highly recommend calling ahead to make sure it isn't closed for a private event.

Absolutely lovely! The garden is spacious and so pretty, with great bottles of wine and an adorable atmosphere. I loved that bug spray was offered upon walking outside because it is a garden, so definitely buggy! For that, I recommend wearing long pants or a dress to cover the legs. I had no problems and had a long jumpsuit on.
Such a beautiful place
What a great last-minute find! Asked Google where to go in Noda and found this place. Hidden gem!
Our family loves the coffee shop and garden for our lazy Sunday's. All staff we have met are very friendly and helpful with any questions we have. They also carry a good selection of local beer.
Cutest place to get coffee or wine and enjoy the beautiful garden!
I love this place .
Really cute garden and shop. Would be amazing during peak blooming season. Had a glass of cava and strolled around with a friend. Would be a great date night spot as well!
Great little spot. Coffee, wine, beer and lots of spots to sit and chat with friends in the garden.

Really enjoyed a visit to Rosie's with coworkers! It's the perfect place to split a bottle (or two) of wine or have a glass while you read a book or write. There was an event happening while I was there so individuals/organizations are able to rent space. Additionally, the staff was super helpful with picking out a wine that aligns with your tastebuds and the season!
Ecpensive! Nice spot. $10 for glass of house red wine. Yikes! Nice location. Atmosphere. Clean bathroom. Outside area very cool.

Visited at twilight after dinner. We found a beautiful, romantic place with winding paths around a garden strung with lights. There are a variety of places to sit, from picnic tables and garden benches to reclining chairs and patio setups. The limited indoor seating is equally colorful and comfortable if the outdoors isn't your style. Nice hideaway in the middle of downtown Charlotte--highly recommend!
We walked in and not a single employee was to be found. We called around the shop and no one ever came. I can't believe that a business would leave their shop unattended like this.
Iced Teas are excellent and the garden is peaceful and magical...and a great place for fiti ops.
Amazing spot! Live music on Thursdays too.

Was there for tea party had a wonderful morning fellowship and support for staff was AWESOME,  first time in Charlotte at a event that clam my mind and was relaxing in my 22 years of being here. THANK YOU FOR THE EXPERIENCE.

The daily specials and events are so fun! It's a great place to have a girls night, grab a coffee and take a walk through the pathways, buy a few plants, smell the roses. One of my favs places to take friends visiting from out of town.
This place is magical. Great little wine bar hidden away close to downtown Charlotte. Phillip was the best at suggesting wine for us.
This is a great place to spend some time in nature with a nice beverage. The staff was extremely helpful by guiding me to a wine I really enjoyed.

This hidden garden was a nice peaceful respite from the bumbling of the city. Walking in and taking in the smells of the flowers was an idyllic setting for sipping on a nicely crafted cortado.

Rosie's combined a few of my favorite things, hidden gardens, shots of espresso, and an artistic yet homely vibe to set up what turned into a wonderful morning.

I'll most assuredly be back any time I find myself in Charlotte again.
Cuuuuute! Outdoor seating is divine. Sculptures and quiet/private space, I love it. Bring bug spray!
Great relaxing venue

Lost in the garden of versus and other things. As soon as you walk in the lush garden the sculptures, the symphony of birds, and wildlife just engulfed me.

So many different places to get lost in. There is also a shop to buy drinks, plants, and things.

A must see in Charlotte for sure.
A beautiful venue that's tucked away in NODA. Te'jani played live and really added to the evening. Really talented musician.
My go to date spot or Tuesday trivia
Will surpasd your expectations.
One of my newfound favorite coffeeshops in Charlotte. The garden area might be the best workspace in the whole city!

Such a peaceful place full of good vibes!  wine is good and great for sharing. I recommend going to optimist hall and parking there, getting some food to go then walking to Rosie's! They allow outside food. Get a bottle from them, head out to the garden and voila, you got a perfect set up!
Super cute. Great place to take pictures. They even have an area you can buy plants.
Great coffee with a beautiful garden! What more can you ask!!
Been twice and wine selection isn't great. I also like sweet wines and they had ONE to choose from. Limited snacks and they're expensive. Grounds are pretty though.

You will not find any place like this one in the city. A coffee and wine Cafe with an entire block's worth of a sculpted garden a to dine in and walk through. Divine is not a good enough word to describe the experience.
Beautifully serene and super cool for socializing casually or more formally.

Beautiful garden and atmosphere. We went in the morning for coffee but can only imagine how beautiful the garden is at night with all of the lights. Barista was very friendly and seemed knowledgeable.
Very nice vibe
We love Rosie's! The coffee and wine is great. Love this atmosphere. Whenever we have out of town family we always bring them and they love this spot!
Boyfriend and I loved it.. . Romantic, chill, beautiful

I was recommended Rosie's as a place to get out of the house to work as I WFH full-time. My friend and I met up on a Friday to work a half day and it was absolutely perfect. The shop was lively, but quiet enough to work, and after work, we sat in the stunning gardens and had a bottle of wine. It looks like they also host a yoga session on Friday mornings which I will absolutely be back to try. Our barista was also very sweet. I highly recommend visiting on a beautiful, sunny day and enjoying what the gardens have to offer.
Tranquil with indoor and outdoor seating

Honestly my favorite place in Charlotte! They have a well curated wine list. The employees are very friendly and are knowledgeable of their selection and offerings. They have coffee and tea on top of the wine. They also leave the loose leaf tea bag in the cup so you can refill for free, which is a huge plus. The garden is cute and quaint.
It could use a bit of spring cleaning but it's a cute spot.
Great place and the park takes it to a whole other level

This place is a gem, the coffee is fantastic with milk from happy cows if you so desire.  Knowledgeable and friendly staff on wine selection as well.  Inside is quaint and cute, suitable to work from a laptop at as they have free wifi as well.  But you should really go sit outside, it's a beautiful setting among rose gardens with tables and benches setup throughout.  Games are available, and feel free to bring your own food or munchies.  Live music on Thursdays.  I kind of hate telling people, this is such a great place I want it all to myself but it should be enjoyed by all.  Go soon, go often.
Great outdoor area with lights and fire pits. Great choices of wine

A night out with #QuantumDionysus my tribe my crew... at first I was not truly interested bc parking is horrible... it's very limited and directions for folks unfamiliar with the area suck for the overflow parking at the Cats garage.  Other than that... I L.O.V.E thiiis space.  The garden is perfect for date night/ girls night or quiet solo time.  The iced decaf coffee was delicious.  The wine options are great. They had live music which we danced to around the firepit. We ordered pizza to be delivered and I bought a S'mores Kit!!!! Omg the best s'mores I've ever had. Thre energy was cool.  Everyone was helpful.  My sisters and I got to love on each other with affirmations and such.  It was a perfect space for healing and positive vibes ! And I drank edible glitter!!!
Enchanting
Beautiful space and friendly staff!
I had really great coffee here, and the grounds are nice.
Overpriced, paying for the garden. Order hot cider, he took it right out of the jug. Tea was terrible too.
Lovely coffee shop with friendly/helpful baristas. Walking inside feels like a warm hug. Walking outside to gorgeous gardens accompanies a tasty beverage perfectly.

One of the cutest spots in town! There's a nice selection of wines that you can buy by the glass or the bottle, or you can get a fresh cup of coffee. Then take your beverage outside and enjoy the stunning gardens!!
Amazing place , I'd love to visit it again whenever I'm in South Carolina

Today was my first time visiting Rosie's and I'll have to say, I'll definitely be back! The atmosphere was so eclectic and unique. I wish I'd been able to visit in the spring or summer so it could have been nicer outside but it wasn't too cold to enjoy the gardens. I went for coffee but they have a huge selection of beverages. I was meeting a relocation client there, who is moving from New Jersey, and it was so easy to chat about her real estate needs. I would recommend Rosie's to anyone looking for somewhere to grab a coffee while enjoying a great atmosphere.
Beautiful spot for a date or drink.  They have wine, beer, coffee.  Plenty of seating all around the garden and can find a more secluded area.
I loved it i definitely recommend it
An idyllic spot to consume caffeine, wine, and conversation. The garden was beautiful and the wine selection pleasing. Bring a book and enjoy!

This was such a pretty place. What a great little spot to meet up with a group of people and drink some wine and bring your own snacks. They had an event there today called the boozy brunch and it was really fun.
Very cute place to relax in the evening, great trivia

This venue is nice. However, I live across the street & I wake up for work at 5 AM. The music is so loud it protrudes into my apartment. There is no consideration. On the website it reflects it should be closed on a Sunday at 8 am. It is 9:28PM and the music is still going. We all love to have fun but can you lower the music for the residential living right next to you? I'm filing a complaint with the city. This is a nightmare ordeal.

Gorgeous garden with plenty of outdoor space for larger groups and smaller tables for couples.  You can grab a glass of wine, beer or a coffee but they've also got plenty of wine by the bottle options as well.  They typically have heaters in the winter so it's even a great place on a cooler evening.  It is a fun place to explore and the laid back vibe makes it a great space for dates or catching up with friends.
Hidden Gem. Gorgeous gardens with a very relaxing feel. I could have stayed for hours.
Beautiful! Good wine and good times
Beautiful outdoor seating and fun trivia night

Stumbled upon this place one late Friday night. Possibly the most ethereal, magical place I've ever been to!! Good selection of wines. I want to come back for their coffee sometime. The staff was super cool too. Lots of seating options outside, good music, great vibes. The garden at night was so beautiful, like a pretty summer garden party. 12/10
Awesome place, beautiful garden area with plenty of plants and cool seating areas! The coffee is pretty good as well!
Their coffee is OK. The garden is lovely with plenty of room to social distance.

We had our first visit here today. This spot has a cool vibe. My wife and i chose the Vinabade Albarino, a delightful Spanish white wine with deep stone fruit aromas, and just the right acidity. We enjoyed our wine in a beautiful garden setting. This spot is a must for your wine experience in NODA. They offer an affordable, yet dynamic wine list, filled with all kinds of goodies! Thank you Dan and staff for a 5 star experience. We will be back!
Great place to sip wine! Very eclectic selection by the glass and a huge shady garden to sit and sip. Staff is very knowledgeable and friendly.
Beautiful garden. Nice selection of wines. Good coffee. I'll definitely be back.
Family place and good for make a picnic!!
What a wonderful environment for downtown. This will become a usual spot for us!
Beautiful rose garden in downtown Charlotte with Wine and Coffee!
Beautiful space in the garden to drink wine. Just lovely. Go there.
Super cute garden, plus live music, and great wine, coffee, and tea options. What's not to love?

Beautiful garden space, with quite the eclectic (in a good way) mix of flowers, plants trees lights and a old train car. It's all laid out nicely so you can feel like you have your own space to sit and talk, even if there are people just a few feet away. after we ordered se coffee, my wife and I with our dog enjoyed strolling throughout and seeing the different part of the garden as we sipped. Both of our coffees(and iced latte and iced chai) were  heavy on the milk, and we probably wouldn't order again, but the ambiance of the garden more than made up for that. We will probably be back in the evening for a glass of wine instead, as it seems the perfect place to relax after a workday.
Great chill found here!
Lovely spot to relax and grab a drink.
Barista was very friendly today, and made a delicious latte. Had a wonderful time walking in the garden while enjoying my coffee with a friend.
I cannot wait to return.  What's better than enjoying a glass of wine in a beautiful garden?
lindo sitio para una conversacion y un cafe
Could this be? Perhaps Charlotte's best kept secret
Hidden gem!
What a lovely hidden gem. The garden is absolutely beautiful. It is lovely to stroll around with a delicious glass of wine. The owners are very nice. We had a great experience here.

This place has a great atmosphere!  Good wine selection and a great place to hang out and talk.  I suggest you skip the small parking lot in the evening and go straight to the cats parking structure behind the building.  Just take McGill from Davidson st, it's across from the park and a short walk.
Perfect for any gathering. The only serve drinks but you can bring your own food!!

Very delightful place. The barista was great.
Unfortunately the garden wasn't in bloom. Still a nice garden spot to enjoy some peace and nature with a hot cup of Chai tea.

Rosie's is the best little gem in Charlotte. The wine selection is great. The gardens are beautiful and secluded. The staff is always friendly and attentive. Kelvin, in particular, has been so damn personable that you feel like you stepped into a good friend's backyard. That's why we prefer the Rosie's atmosphere over any other bar/cafe/outdoor setting in Charlotte. They're also great with Covid precautions and you can feel safe enjoying your wine or coffee in a place where staff have taken measures to limit risk.
Great coffee and amazing out door seating!
Always a wonderful environment to sit and enjoy friends.
Great coffee selection! Beautiful environment with friendly community. One of my all time favorite places in Charlotte.

This lovely little slice of heaven is just outside uptown! Attracts a LOT of people, but we were still able to have a good socially distanced time together.

On a side note, it was wonderful to smell the boxwood bushes. Reminds me of colonial gardens!

The territory is wow ! Coffee is ok.
I like the atmosphere
So cozy! Great wine!

This place is a hidden gem in the Charlotte area. Great wine and coffee. This place is amazing and wonderful place to relax. Awesome garden to hang and take a relaxing break from the city. If you are need for a secret garden, this is the place!!
What a cool place, with the rose gardens outside (The McGill Rose Garden) a great place to be outside, chill and enjoy their wine/coffee! Beautiful hidden gem right outside uptown I-277 loop!!
Adorable coffee and wine shop. Get a glass or bottle and sit amongst the flowers. They have coffee, wine and beer.
We can't wait to visit in the spring and summer! Staff is welcoming and the garden is gorgeous at night.

Went to Rosie's for a drink before my birthday dinner. It was cold outside, but there were heaters and fire pits to keep us warm. The atmosphere was lovely and COVID-friendly. Ordering was easy and the staff were kind and courteous. Definitely a new favorite spot.
Super cute place. The garden is beautiful at night. Can't wait to go back.
This place is amazing! So beautiful  it's a great place to hang out next to the fire surrounded by nature.

Loved this place and the concept. We came in on a Thursday and enjoyed their special $12 flight. I deff recommend the red ones, specially the Malbec.
They set up the fire by our table and we enjoyed some dessert we had brought in. Staff members were attentive and welcoming.
We had a chance to walk around a bit and would love to see this place in daylight too.
Beautiful... Dusk is the time to be here...
Great little spot adjacent to the park. Good selection of drinks that you can go sit by the fire or a heater outside and enjoy the night.

This place is a hidden gem! Such a quiet and calm atmosphere to enjoy some wine or a beer in a socially distant way. The garden itself is huge with plenty of hidden tables and artwork. The lights, fires, and heating lamps make it a perfect place to stay into the evening. They have a nice wine selection and incredibly helpful and kind staff!

Rosie's Wine Garden was previously only open for private parties, weddings and the like. If you want to go out to enjoy a glass or two of wine with friends or that special someone this place has excellent ambiance and a great variety of domestic and International wines.
Incredible atmosphere outside among the gardens with a nice glass of wine
